<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020</DATELINE><TITLE>Pediatric Middle East Respiratory Syndrome Coronavirus (MERS-CoV) Infection â€“ UAE | Directory of Open Access Journals</TITLE><BODY>Introduction In 2012, MERS-CoV was identified in Saudi Arabia and resulted in more than 2442 confirmed cases worldwide by May 2019. MERS-CoV infection in children is less common. A review of MERS-CoV in children from 2012 to April 2016 summarized the clinical manifestation of 31 reported cases. Most children were asymptomatic or had mild respiratory symptoms, and severe infection reported in patients with comorbid conditions. We aimed to study the clinical characteristics of pediatric MERS CoV infected cases in UAE supported by literature review.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>